# RoundTable Framework — Code Ownership
# https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners
#
# IMPORTANT: CODEOWNERS uses the LAST matching pattern, not the first.
# More specific patterns must come AFTER general ones.
#
# Security model updated after xMartin PR #22 incident:
# - Unauthorized folder (10. GitHubReference/) was added to TeamDocument
# - CODEOWNERS was too permissive on .claude/TeamDocument/ (co-owner could self-approve)
# - Executable files (hooks, workflows) had insufficient ownership protection

# ============================================================
# TIER 1: CRITICAL — Owner ONLY (@VarakornUnicornTech)
# These files can execute code, modify AI behavior, or
# compromise security. NO contributor can modify these
# without explicit Owner review.
# ============================================================

# Executable scripts — can run arbitrary commands on user machines
/hooks/                                @VarakornUnicornTech

# CI/CD pipelines — can exfiltrate secrets, run malicious code
/.github/workflows/                    @VarakornUnicornTech
/.github/CODEOWNERS                    @VarakornUnicornTech

# AI behavior control — prompt-level governance
/.claude/rules/                        @VarakornUnicornTech
/.claude/settings.json                 @VarakornUnicornTech

# External service configuration
/.mcp.json                             @VarakornUnicornTech

# Plugin manifest — controls what gets loaded
/plugin.json                           @VarakornUnicornTech

# Framework identity and versioning
/.claude/CLAUDE.md                     @VarakornUnicornTech
/.claude/agents/                       @VarakornUnicornTech
/template-version.json                 @VarakornUnicornTech

# Legal and governance
/LICENSE                               @VarakornUnicornTech
/GOVERNANCE.md                         @VarakornUnicornTech
/SECURITY.md                           @VarakornUnicornTech
/MAINTAINERS.md                        @VarakornUnicornTech

# ============================================================
# TIER 2: PROTECTED — Owner + Approved Maintainers
# Content changes allowed with maintainer review.
# New subdirectories require Owner approval (enforced by CI).
# ============================================================

# Policy files (existing subdirectories only)
/.claude/policies/                     @VarakornUnicornTech @xMartin14091x
/.claude/TeamDocument/1. Policies/     @VarakornUnicornTech @xMartin14091x
/.claude/TeamDocument/2. TeamChat/     @VarakornUnicornTech @xMartin14091x

# Skill definitions
/.claude/skills/                       @VarakornUnicornTech @xMartin14091x

# Primary documentation
/CHANGELOG.md                          @VarakornUnicornTech @xMartin14091x
/README.md                             @VarakornUnicornTech @xMartin14091x
/README.th.md                          @VarakornUnicornTech @xMartin14091x

# ============================================================
# TIER 2.5: TeamDocument CATCH-ALL — Owner ONLY
# Any new folder under TeamDocument/ (like 10. GitHubReference/)
# that doesn't match Tier 2 patterns above requires Owner review.
# This MUST come AFTER the specific Tier 2 TeamDocument patterns.
# ============================================================

/.claude/TeamDocument/                 @VarakornUnicornTech

